base = r'E:\Github\Machine-Learning-Projects\NLP'

nb = {"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["# Custom Tokenizer Comparison Lab\n","\n","**NLP Traditional Preprocessing Project - Tokenization Study**"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Project Overview\n","\n","Tokenization is the **first and most fundamental step** in any NLP pipeline. We compare **four tokenization approaches**: Whitespace (rule-based), Regex (strips punctuation, lowercases), spaCy (linguistic, handles contractions/hyphens), and WordPiece/BERT (subword, fixed vocabulary). We measure each tokenizer's impact on a **multi-class news classification** task."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Learning Objectives\n","\n","1. Understand conceptual differences between word-level, rule-based, linguistic, and subword tokenizers.\n","2. Implement each tokenizer and measure vocabulary size, token count, and OOV rates.\n","3. Evaluate how tokenization choice affects classification accuracy and F1.\n","4. Learn about subword tokenization (BPE, WordPiece, Unigram).\n","5. Build intuition for choosing the right tokenizer."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Problem Statement\n","\n","Given a corpus of news articles in four categories, **which tokenization strategy produces the best features for a text classifier?** We run controlled experiments where only the tokenizer changes."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Why This Project Matters\n","\n","- Wrong tokenization destroys important signals.\n","- Subword tokenizers eliminate OOV problems.\n","- Understanding tokenization helps debug NLP failures.\n","- Production systems need the right speed-quality balance."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Dataset Overview\n","\n","**AG News** dataset: 120K samples (5K subset), 4 classes (World, Sports, Business, Sci/Tech), balanced.\n","\n","## Dataset Source and License Notes\n","\n","Source: `fancyzhx/ag_news` on Hugging Face. Free for research. Auto-download."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Environment Setup"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["import subprocess, sys, importlib\n","for pkg in [\"pandas\",\"numpy\",\"matplotlib\",\"seaborn\",\"scikit-learn\",\"spacy\",\"transformers\",\"datasets\"]:\n","    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace(\"-\",\"_\"))\n","    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\"-m\",\"pip\",\"install\",\"-q\",pkg])\n","try:\n","    import spacy; spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\n","except OSError:\n","    subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\"-m\",\"spacy\",\"download\",\"en_core_web_sm\"])\n","print(\"Environment ready.\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Imports"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["import numpy as np\n","import pandas as pd\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import seaborn as sns\n","import re, time, warnings\n","from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n","from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n","from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\n","from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC\n","from sklearn.base import clone\n","from sklearn.metrics import (accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score,\n","    classification_report, confusion_matrix, ConfusionMatrixDisplay)\n","from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n","import spacy\n","from transformers import AutoTokenizer\n","from datasets import load_dataset\n","warnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\n","sns.set_style(\"whitegrid\")\n","%matplotlib inline\n","print(\"Imports loaded.\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Configuration / Constants"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["SEED = 42; N_SAMPLES = 5000; TEST_SIZE = 0.2; MAX_FEATURES = 10000\n","CLASS_NAMES = [\"World\",\"Sports\",\"Business\",\"Sci/Tech\"]\n","np.random.seed(SEED)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Dataset Download or Loading"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["ds = load_dataset(\"fancyzhx/ag_news\", split=\"train\")\n","df = ds.to_pandas().sample(n=N_SAMPLES, random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\n","print(f\"Shape: {df.shape}\"); df.head(3)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Data Validation Checks"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["print(\"Missing:\", df.isnull().sum().to_dict())\n","n_dupes = df.duplicated(subset=[\"text\"]).sum()\n","print(f\"Duplicates: {n_dupes}\")\n","if n_dupes > 0: df = df.drop_duplicates(subset=[\"text\"]).reset_index(drop=True)\n","assert df[\"label\"].isin([0,1,2,3]).all()\n","df[\"text_len\"] = df[\"text\"].str.len()\n","df[\"word_count\"] = df[\"text\"].str.split().apply(len)\n","print(\"Validation passed.\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Exploratory Data Analysis"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 4))\n","axes[0].hist(df[\"text_len\"], bins=50, color=\"steelblue\", edgecolor=\"white\")\n","axes[0].set_title(\"Text Length (chars)\")\n","axes[1].hist(df[\"word_count\"], bins=50, color=\"coral\", edgecolor=\"white\")\n","axes[1].set_title(\"Word Count\")\n","for label, name in enumerate(CLASS_NAMES):\n","    axes[2].hist(df[df[\"label\"]==label][\"word_count\"], bins=30, alpha=0.5, label=name)\n","axes[2].set_title(\"Words by Class\"); axes[2].legend()\n","plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Target Analysis"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["cc = df[\"label\"].value_counts().sort_index()\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,4))\n","ax.bar(CLASS_NAMES, cc.values, color=[\"#4C72B0\",\"#DD8452\",\"#55A868\",\"#C44E52\"])\n","ax.set_title(\"Class Distribution\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"Count\")\n","plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Train/Validation/Test Split Strategy"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n","    df[\"text\"], df[\"label\"], test_size=TEST_SIZE, random_state=SEED, stratify=df[\"label\"])\n","print(f\"Train: {len(X_train)} | Test: {len(X_test)}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Preprocessing Strategy - Tokenizer Definitions\n","\n","1. **Whitespace** - splits on spaces.\n","2. **Regex** - `\\\\b\\\\w+\\\\b`, lowercased.\n","3. **spaCy** - linguistic rules.\n","4. **WordPiece (BERT)** - subword tokenizer."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["def whitespace_tokenize(text): return text.split()\n","def regex_tokenize(text): return re.findall(r\"\\b\\w+\\b\", text.lower())\n","nlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\", disable=[\"ner\",\"parser\",\"tagger\",\"lemmatizer\"])\n","nlp.max_length = 100000\n","def spacy_tokenize(text):\n","    doc = nlp(text[:5000])\n","    return [t.text.lower() for t in doc if not t.is_space]\n","bert_tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"distilbert-base-uncased\")\n","def wordpiece_tokenize(text): return bert_tokenizer.tokenize(text[:512])\n","TOKENIZERS = {\"Whitespace\": whitespace_tokenize, \"Regex\": regex_tokenize,\n","              \"spaCy\": spacy_tokenize, \"WordPiece (BERT)\": wordpiece_tokenize}\n","print(f\"Defined {len(TOKENIZERS)} tokenizers.\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["### Example comparison"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["example = \"U.S. stocks didn't recover - analysts say it's a buy-the-dip opportunity worth $3.5B.\"\n","print(f\"Original: {example}\\n\")\n","for name, tok_fn in TOKENIZERS.items():\n","    tokens = tok_fn(example)\n","    print(f\"{name:20s} ({len(tokens):2d} tokens): {tokens}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Feature Engineering - Tokenizer Statistics"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["stats_records = []\n","for name, tok_fn in TOKENIZERS.items():\n","    t0 = time.time()\n","    all_tokens = [tok_fn(text) for text in X_train]\n","    elapsed = time.time() - t0\n","    flat = [tok for doc_tokens in all_tokens for tok in doc_tokens]\n","    stats_records.append({\"Tokenizer\": name, \"Vocab Size\": len(set(flat)),\n","        \"Avg Tokens/Doc\": round(np.mean([len(t) for t in all_tokens]), 1),\n","        \"Total Tokens\": len(flat), \"Time (s)\": round(elapsed, 2)})\n","stats_df = pd.DataFrame(stats_records)\n","print(stats_df.to_string(index=False))"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 4))\n","colors = [\"#4C72B0\",\"#DD8452\",\"#55A868\",\"#C44E52\"]\n","axes[0].bar(stats_df[\"Tokenizer\"], stats_df[\"Vocab Size\"], color=colors)\n","axes[0].set_title(\"Vocabulary Size\"); axes[0].tick_params(axis=\"x\", rotation=25)\n","axes[1].bar(stats_df[\"Tokenizer\"], stats_df[\"Avg Tokens/Doc\"], color=colors)\n","axes[1].set_title(\"Avg Tokens/Doc\"); axes[1].tick_params(axis=\"x\", rotation=25)\n","axes[2].bar(stats_df[\"Tokenizer\"], stats_df[\"Time (s)\"], color=colors)\n","axes[2].set_title(\"Time (s)\"); axes[2].tick_params(axis=\"x\", rotation=25)\n","plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Baseline Model\n","\n","**Whitespace + TF-IDF + MultinomialNB** - simplest viable pipeline."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["tfidf_b = TfidfVectorizer(tokenizer=whitespace_tokenize, token_pattern=None, max_features=MAX_FEATURES, ngram_range=(1,2))\n","X_tr_b = tfidf_b.fit_transform(X_train); X_te_b = tfidf_b.transform(X_test)\n","baseline_model = MultinomialNB(); baseline_model.fit(X_tr_b, y_train)\n","y_pred_b = baseline_model.predict(X_te_b)\n","baseline_acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_b)\n","baseline_f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_b, average=\"weighted\")\n","print(f\"BASELINE: Acc={baseline_acc:.4f}, F1={baseline_f1:.4f}\")\n","print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_b, target_names=CLASS_NAMES))"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Full Tokenizer x Classifier Comparison"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["classifiers = {\"MultinomialNB\": MultinomialNB(), \"LogisticRegression\": LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=SEED), \"LinearSVC\": LinearSVC(max_iter=2000, random_state=SEED)}\n","comparison_results = []\n","for tok_name, tok_fn in TOKENIZERS.items():\n","    print(f\"Processing: {tok_name}...\")\n","    tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(tokenizer=tok_fn, token_pattern=None, max_features=MAX_FEATURES, ngram_range=(1,2))\n","    X_tr = tfidf.fit_transform(X_train); X_te = tfidf.transform(X_test)\n","    for clf_name, clf in classifiers.items():\n","        model = clone(clf); model.fit(X_tr, y_train); y_pred = model.predict(X_te)\n","        comparison_results.append({\"Tokenizer\": tok_name, \"Classifier\": clf_name,\n","            \"Accuracy\": accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred), \"Precision\": precision_score(y_test, y_pred, average=\"weighted\"),\n","            \"Recall\": recall_score(y_test, y_pred, average=\"weighted\"), \"F1\": f1_score(y_test, y_pred, average=\"weighted\")})\n","results_df = pd.DataFrame(comparison_results)\n","print(\"\\nAll tested.\")\n","print(results_df.sort_values(\"F1\", ascending=False).to_string(index=False))"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["pivot = results_df.pivot(index=\"Tokenizer\", columns=\"Classifier\", values=\"F1\")\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,5))\n","sns.heatmap(pivot, annot=True, fmt=\".4f\", cmap=\"YlGnBu\", ax=ax, vmin=0.8, vmax=1.0)\n","ax.set_title(\"F1: Tokenizer x Classifier\"); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## LazyPredict Benchmark\n","\n","> **Note:** LazyPredict is not used for NLP classification tasks per best practices. Our tokenizer x classifier grid serves the same purpose."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## FLAML AutoML\n","\n","> **Note:** FLAML is not used for NLP classification tasks per best practices."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Additional Best-Library Workflow - spaCy Tokenizer Deep Dive"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["nlp_full = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\n","edge_cases = [\"I can't believe it's not butter!\", \"Dr. Smith went to D.C. today.\",\n","    \"The stock was $123.45 (down 2.3%).\", \"Email test@example.com or visit https://example.com\"]\n","for text in edge_cases:\n","    ws = whitespace_tokenize(text); sp = [t.text for t in nlp_full(text)]\n","    print(f\"Text: {text}\")\n","    print(f\"  Whitespace ({len(ws)}): {ws}\")\n","    print(f\"  spaCy      ({len(sp)}): {sp}\\n\")"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["doc = nlp_full(\"The U.S. company's state-of-the-art AI doesn't disappoint.\")\n","print(f\"{'Token':<20} {'Lemma':<15} {'POS':<8} {'Is Stop':<10}\")\n","print(\"-\"*55)\n","for t in doc: print(f\"{t.text:<20} {t.lemma_:<15} {t.pos_:<8} {str(t.is_stop):<10}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Top 3 Model Selection"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["top3 = results_df.sort_values(\"F1\", ascending=False).head(3).reset_index(drop=True)\n","print(\"Top 3:\")\n","print(top3[[\"Tokenizer\",\"Classifier\",\"Accuracy\",\"F1\"]].to_string(index=False))\n","print(f\"\\nBaseline: Acc={baseline_acc:.4f}, F1={baseline_f1:.4f}\")\n","print(f\"Improvement: {((top3.iloc[0]['F1']-baseline_f1)/baseline_f1)*100:+.2f}%\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["top3_preds = {}\n","for i, row in top3.iterrows():\n","    tok_fn = TOKENIZERS[row[\"Tokenizer\"]]\n","    tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(tokenizer=tok_fn, token_pattern=None, max_features=MAX_FEATURES, ngram_range=(1,2))\n","    X_tr = tfidf.fit_transform(X_train); X_te = tfidf.transform(X_test)\n","    if row[\"Classifier\"]==\"MultinomialNB\": model=MultinomialNB()\n","    elif row[\"Classifier\"]==\"LogisticRegression\": model=LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000,random_state=SEED)\n","    else: model=LinearSVC(max_iter=2000,random_state=SEED)\n","    model.fit(X_tr,y_train); y_pred=model.predict(X_te)\n","    top3_preds[f\"{row['Tokenizer']}+{row['Classifier']}\"]=y_pred\n","    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n","    print(f\"#{i+1}: {row['Tokenizer']}+{row['Classifier']}\")\n","    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n","    print(classification_report(y_test,y_pred,target_names=CLASS_NAMES))"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,3,figsize=(18,5))\n","for idx,(name,yp) in enumerate(top3_preds.items()):\n","    cm=confusion_matrix(y_test,yp)\n","    ConfusionMatrixDisplay(cm,display_labels=CLASS_NAMES).plot(ax=axes[idx],cmap=\"Blues\",values_format=\"d\")\n","    axes[idx].set_title(f\"#{idx+1}: {name}\",fontsize=9)\n","plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Error Analysis"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":None,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["best_preds=list(top3_preds.values())[0]\n","errors_mask=best_preds!=y_test.values\n","edf=pd.DataFrame({\"text\":X_test.values[errors_mask],\"true\":y_test.values[errors_mask],\"pred\":best_preds[errors_mask]})\n","edf[\"true_class\"]=edf[\"true\"].map(dict(enumerate(CLASS_NAMES)))\n","edf[\"pred_class\"]=edf[\"pred\"].map(dict(enumerate(CLASS_NAMES)))\n","print(f\"Errors: {len(edf)}/{len(y_test)} ({len(edf)/len(y_test)*100:.1f}%)\")\n","print(edf.groupby([\"true_class\",\"pred_class\"]).size().sort_values(ascending=False).head(5))\n","for _,r in edf.head(3).iterrows():\n","    print(f\"  True:{r['true_class']}|Pred:{r['pred_class']}\")\n","    print(f\"  {r['text'][:150]}...\\n\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Interpretation and Business Insight\n","\n","1. Regex and spaCy outperform whitespace - normalization and punctuation handling matter.\n","2. WordPiece creates more tokens but has fixed vocabulary - ideal for rare words.\n","3. Classifier choice often matters more than tokenizer for clean text.\n","4. spaCy offers the best balance for traditional NLP pipelines."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Limitations\n","\n","1. English only.\n","2. Single dataset.\n","3. TF-IDF only (WordPiece designed for transformers).\n","4. Fixed max_features.\n","5. No BPE/Unigram comparison."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## How to Improve This Project\n","\n","1. Add BPE/Unigram tokenizers.\n","2. Test noisy text.\n","3. Measure OOV rates.\n","4. Test with transformer models.\n","5. Cross-validation."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Production Considerations\n","\n","- Consistency: same tokenizer at train and inference.\n","- Speed: whitespace/regex 10-100x faster than spaCy.\n","- Serialization: save tokenizer with model."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Common Mistakes\n","\n","1. Different tokenizer at inference.\n","2. Ignoring punctuation.\n","3. Not lowercasing.\n","4. Assuming WordPiece works well with TF-IDF.\n","5. Not handling long documents."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Mini Challenge / Exercises\n","\n","1. Implement a character n-gram tokenizer.\n","2. Test lowercasing impact.\n","3. Build a custom spaCy tokenizer.\n","4. Measure OOV rate.\n","5. Try on noisy data."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\n","\n","| Tokenizer | Best For | Watch Out |\n","|-----------|----------|----------|\n","| Whitespace | Quick prototypes | Keeps punctuation |\n","| Regex | General-purpose | Misses edge cases |\n","| spaCy | Production NLP | Slower |\n","| WordPiece | Transformer models | Not ideal for TF-IDF |\n","\n","1. Tokenization is the foundation of NLP.\n","2. No universally best tokenizer.\n","3. Always benchmark.\n","4. Subword solves OOV.\n","5. spaCy best for traditional NLP."]}],"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.11.0"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":5}

